abstract: Doug Emhoff, the husband of Vice President Kamala Harris, has become a forceful voice against what he called an “epidemic of hate” against the Jewish community.
snippet: Doug Emhoff, the husband of Vice President Kamala Harris, has become a forceful voice against what he called an “epidemic of hate” against the Jewish community.

abstract: The bloc’s antitrust regulators could side with Microsoft on Monday, but the tech giant still faces an uphill battle to gaining full  approval.
snippet: The bloc’s antitrust regulators could side with Microsoft on Monday, but the tech giant still faces an uphill battle to gaining full  approval.
lead_paragraph: European antitrust regulators are set to weigh in Monday on Microsoft’s $69 billion takeover of Activision Blizzard. In a twist, the European Commission is reportedly set to approve a video game megadeal that its American and British counterparts have already rejected.

main: The $69 Billion Microsoft-Activision Deal Faces a Big E.U. Test

abstract: The close alliance that has developed between the speaker and the hard-right Georgia Republican explains his rise, how he might govern and the heavy influence of the extremes on the new House G.O.P. majority.
snippet: The close alliance that has developed between the speaker and the hard-right Georgia Republican explains his rise, how he might govern and the heavy influence of the extremes on the new House G.O.P. majority.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Days after he won his gavel in a protracted fight with hard-right Republicans, Speaker Kevin McCarthy gushed to a friend about the ironclad bond he had developed with an unlikely ally in his battle for political survival, Representative Marjorie Taylor Greene of Georgia.

main: How Kevin McCarthy Forged an Ironclad Bond With Marjorie Taylor Greene
print_headline: Speaker’s Union With Firebrand May Shape G.O.P.

abstract: The Securities and Exchange Commission ended its investigation into former Senator Richard Burr, three years after he sold more than $1.6 million in stocks following Covid-19 briefings.
snippet: The Securities and Exchange Commission ended its investigation into former Senator Richard Burr, three years after he sold more than $1.6 million in stocks following Covid-19 briefings.
lead_paragraph: The Securities and Exchange Commission has closed an investigation into former Senator Richard M. Burr that examined whether a series of stock sales he made in early 2020 after being briefed on the threat of Covid-19 were improper, Mr. Burr and his lawyer said on Friday.

main: S.E.C. Inquiry Into Former Senator’s Stock Sales Is Closed Without Charges
print_headline: S.E.C. Closes Investigation Of Stock Sales Of Ex-Senator

abstract: Scientists are working to improve the breeding success of the condor. Their secret assistant: a plastic, 3-D printed, sensor-laden “smart egg.”
snippet: Scientists are working to improve the breeding success of the condor. Their secret assistant: a plastic, 3-D printed, sensor-laden “smart egg.”
lead_paragraph: For two months this spring, a pair of California condor parents carefully tended to a single, enormous egg. They took turns sitting on the egg to keep it warm, and they routinely rotated the egg, a behavior believed to promote proper chick development.

main: How a High-Tech Egg Could Help the Endangered California Condor
print_headline: Tricking Expectant Condors, and Proud of It

abstract: As Russia pressures local residents to leave, a hydroelectric dam outside the city may prove to be a major point of contention.

lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — With the city of Kherson shaping up to be the site of the next major battle in Ukraine, occupying forces there raised the pressure on residents Wednesday to abandon their homes and leave for Russia, warning that if they stayed they would be considered hostile and treated accordingly.

main: Reports of Looting in Kherson as Ukrainians Battle to Retake the City
print_headline: Ukrainians Try to Retake Kherson and Nearby Hydroelectric Dam
